Step-by-Step Execution in Exam
✅ STEP 1 — Create New Project (SPECIAL TEMPLATE!)

Open Android Studio → New Project
⚠️ Select "Google Maps Activity" (NOT Empty Activity!)
Name: GoogleMapDemo
Package: com.example.googlemapdemo
Language: Java
Min SDK: API 21
Click Finish → Wait for Gradle


✅ STEP 2 — Get Google Maps API Key

⚠️ In exam — API key may already be provided in the code. If not, follow these steps:


After project creates, look in left panel:
Go to: app → res → values → google_maps_api.xml
You'll see a long URL — copy it
Open browser → Paste URL → Press Enter
Google Console opens → Click "Create Project" → "Continue"
Click "Create API Key"
Copy the generated API key (starts with AIza...)
Come back to Android Studio
In google_maps_api.xml, replace YOUR_KEY_HERE with your API key


✅ STEP 3 — Check google_maps_api.xml
xml<!-- This file is auto-generated -->
<resources>
    <string name="google_maps_key" 
        templateMergeStrategy="preserve"
        translatable="false">YOUR_API_KEY_HERE</string>
</resources>
Replace YOUR_API_KEY_HERE with the copied key.
